Fixes #18678

When given a simple plugin like this:
```js
export default {
  content: [{ raw: '!a' },],
  plugins: [
    ({ addBase }) => addBase({
      '@media (min-width: 1728px)': {
        '.a': { 'padding-top': '1rem !important' },
        '.b': { 'padding-right': '1rem !important' },
      }
    }),
  ],
}
```

If this plugin saw the utility `!a` it would correctly modify both rules to eliminate any irrelevant classes. Unfortunately, in the case of the 2nd rule this meant it's left with an empty selector which is invalid.

We now detect this case and remove the rule if that happens.

Fixes #4094

This PR adds support for specifying raw content as part of the `purge` config, mimicking [the PurgeCSS API](https://purgecss.com/configuration.html#options):

```js
module.exports = {
  purge: [
    './src/**/*.html',
    { raw: '<div class="bg-red-500"></div>' },
  ],
}
```

You can also specify an extension which is used to select the appropriate extractor:

```js
module.exports = {
  purge: {
    content: [
      {
        raw: '<div class="bg-red-500"></div>',
        extension: 'html',
      },
    ],
    options: {
      extractors: [
        {
          extractor: (content) => { /* ... */ },
          extensions: ['html'],
        },
      ],
    },
  },
}
```
